  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ILFE:Desarrollo econ&#xF3;mico productivo de familias de 4 comunidades en Somoto</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities associated with this project include:

-training on climate smart agricultural practices and improved infrastructure for irrigation (well and irrigation systems)

-creation of a community based organization to process and transform agricultural products within the community as well as basic infrastructure for processing and marketing

-workshops with men and women to analyze gender roles and impacts within the household and farm enterprise</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will improve the quality of life for 579 members of 120 families and indirectly benefit 217 additional residents of these communities through improved yields of food and commercial crops, adding value within the community through community organization around processing and marketing, and improved awareness around gender roles and inequalities within the households. 

Participaing families will directly benefit from:

&#x2022;	Increased and more stable yields, food availability, and income 
&#x2022;	Increased value added and marketing capacity for agricultural products  
&#x2022;	Improved understanding of gender roles in household and productive activities</narrative>
  </description>
